Methods of integrating ICT into the teaching process, planning and designing a web-based course, composing electronic learning materials: presentations, tests and web pages.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce various modern e-learning methods and e-learning programs. To give students an overview of the possibilities of using ICT in education. To introduce different educational systems and the possibilities they offer for different target groups (principals, teachers, tutors, students, parents)Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - is able to plan teaching (including e-learning) to support digital competences and search for relevant information; 
- is able to use digital tools covered during the course in his/her teaching;
- is able to create new and modify existing digital learning materials (texts, images, sound and video, interactive learning materials);
- is aware of possibilities for safe sharing of digital content in the Web;
- understands the importance of copyright rules in creating digital learning materials;
- is able to use different digital communication tools to plan and conduct teaching (e.g., planning and conducting video conferences).
